.@SenSchumer @POTUS one great solution already passed by @HouseGOP is H.R. 2, the Secure the Border Act.  

We welcome you to join Republicans in our efforts to secure the border. Pass H.R. 2 and sign it into law.

Matt Gaetz is nothing more than a chaos agent working with Democrats to halt our progress. This motion to vacate is a sad cry for attention and derails our conservative agenda. I continue to stand with @SpeakerMcCarthy.

From day one, @HouseGOP has delivered conservative wins.

Fighting to close our southern border, protecting parental rights, standing up for our military, and cutting $2T in spending and more.
 
This takes leadership. I stand with @SpeakerMcCarthy.

Now, we have to use the time we have to continue to advance the rest of our appropriations bills. 

We are here to change the reckless status quo in Washington, and I remain committed to delivering that for the American people.
It’s time for the President to wake up and change course and for the Senate to join the House and pass these measures.

The President’s failure at the southern border is one of our nation’s most pressing issues. House Republicans have promised and delivered solutions to this problem in the form of H.R. 2 and the Homeland Security appropriations bill, which I voted in favor of.

Today, I voted for the latest stopgap measure offered by the House. This was not our preferred path forward, but I could not allow our service members, border patrol agents, and the health of our overall economy to shoulder the burden of a government shutdown.

The bill reduced spending to pre-pandemic levels and included H.R. 2, our strongest ever border security package. I remain committed to continue working on solutions for the American people, to secure the border, and to restore fiscal sanity in Washington, D.C.

Today, I voted in favor of the Spending Reduction and Border Security Act. This stop-gap measure would cut spending, secure our border, pay our troops, and create a commission to address our long-term debt.
